MOVE
  Move a commodity between two owned sectors.

SYNTAX
  move <commodity> <from-x,y> <amount> <to-x,y>
  mov  <commodity> <from-x,y> <amount> <to-x,y>

DESCRIPTION
  Transfers goods from one sector to another.  Both sectors must be
  yours.  Moving consumes mobility from the source sector.

  <commodity>  - single letter: f=food c=civ i=iron l=lcm etc.
  <from-x,y>   - source sector coordinates
  <amount>     - how many units to move
  <to-x,y>     - destination sector coordinates

  The sectors do not need to be adjacent; the path is calculated
  automatically through your owned territory.  Each step of the
  path uses mobility.  Moving through a highway (+) sector costs
  less mobility.

  Use the distribution system (info threshold / info distribute)
  for automatic commodity movement each update instead of manual
  moves.

EXAMPLE
  move food 0,0 500 4,-2    move 500 food from capital to farm
  move iron 0,0 200 5,-1    send iron to LCM factory
  move lcm 5,-1 50 6,0      move LCM to harbor for ship building

SEE ALSO
